Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 25;
                                                  written lines: 25; The beginning of Hafṭarot are indicated in the margin of the prophetical books. Masorah, frequently written in the form of ornamental designs, occupies two lines in the upper margin and three lines in lower margin of the page. Several masoretic rubrics at the end of most of the books. Flesh side and hair side are distinguishable.
 Parallel Hebrew foliation on the verso side.
 Unfoliated blank leaf after folio 322. Watermark, folio [fs003], of a of a crowned coat of arms (presumably with a fleur-de-lis and with the monogram 'WR'), similar to 1784 . Watermark, folios [fse004], [fse005], of the monogram 'IHS' with a cross, similar to  1785a.
